        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 8:21PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Milam, or 25 miles northwest of Toledo Bend Dam, moving east at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Milam, Negreet, Sexton, Rosevine, and Hemphill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
